description: You stand in a large lobby of the tower.  The inside looks like it once
was a great tower, but now, it looks like the rest of the city.  The only
exit out is north.
6775.name: North Entrance

description: You are at the entrance of the City Hall Of Zozo.  Before you
stands the city hall that runs Zozo.  The hall is pretty much empty, a
few desks are scattered all around.  Papers seem to blow by you in the
wind...  The walls are made out of black marble, and the room have
only very little light in it.  There are exits to all sides of you.
6849.name: City Hall Of Zozo

description: Some rats here move around hissing at you passing by.  A bum sits here
with a huge jumbo sewer rat on his lap, petting it like it was his dog.
6743.name: {g[ {*No{&rthwe{*st {cAlley {rRoad {g]{x

description: You stand at the Roads Department of Zozo.  A large desk stands in
the corner, in the corner so a person could sit at it and look out
both windows..  The papers on the desk seem to be piling up, and no
one is around to tend to them.  A large map hangs on the wall, torn
down the middle.  From what you can see it is a map of Zozo.
6850.name: The Roads Department

description: This road, an almost trail-like path, leads off away from the city.  It
wanders through dark grass that grows in this odd place between the hills
and the mountains.
6865.name: Outside Alley Road

description: You stand in the Whore's Room.  A whore is laying on the bed, her clothes
lay on the ground.  A dirty adventurer kneels on top of her, making sweet
sweet love.  She moans out with every...  Oops, this is getting too dirty...
6824.name: Whore's Room

description: {^{xYou stand at the bar.  The top of it is lit up like a Christmas tree.
Many many drinks lay behind the bar with a single guy standing here serving
drinks.  Three Glowing Balls sit on shelves tuned into some other place in
the world or some other world.  You see one of them looking at two men
fighting in a coliseum.  {x
6819.name: Bar

description: A piece of wood falls from the ceiling and hits you in the head as you
enter the General Store of ZoZo.  The shelves are lined with anything from
{#mo{2ld{&y ch{2ee{#se{x to broken {6sh{^ar{8d{7s of {8g{^la{6ss{x which likely were once light bulbs.
6770.name: General Store

description: You are between cars 7 and 8.  The only exit is north.
6886.name: Between Car 7 & 8

description: The train does not reach back this far. People are getting on the
caboose which is one north.
6871.name: Railroad Platform

description: You stand in a large lobby of the tower.  The inside looks like it once
was a great tower, but now, it looks like the rest of the city.  The exit
out is east.
6778.name: East Entrance

description: The Elevator Buttons...
You stand inside an elevator. A sign hangs here with the numbers of
floors. The button #9 is lit up.
6790.name: Elevator At Ninth Floor

description: You step into a very large gym.  You see a lot of people working out and
making them buff.  Then you see a big skinny bald guy with a clipboard
screaming out stuff at other people working.  The whole room is cluttered
with equipment that helps you get stronger.
6771.name: Coach Slack's Training Gym

description: You step out of the elevator and into a huge field.  You see some knights
looking up at the clouds.  You see >>> GOD <<< himself talking to them.  He
tells the tale of the quest for the Holy Grail.  Then the clouds close and
he is gone.  The knights mount there horses and ride off.  You see a path
going east.
6828.name: Field Somewhere Outdoor

description: The pain returns to your head and the voice of the
train echos once more.
" YOU HAVE DEFEATED ME THIS TIME. I SHALL LET YOU LIVE "
" BUT THERE IS ONE THING I MUST DO BEFORE WE DEPART TO "
" THE OTHER SIDE "
6892.name: On The Locomotive

description: You smell charcoal as you enter the burnt warehouse.  Ash lays
heavily on the floor.  There is a man sobing in the corner.
6897.name: The Burnt Warehouse

description: You fall out onto the lawn.  You stand in front of a large castle where
the knights talk to some other knights on the castle.  You hear them talk
and notice that they speak with a French accent.  They taunt and make fun of
the brave knights below only to eject a large cow at them.  They stand there
cackling and throwing all kinds of stuff at the knights.
6832.name: At The French Castle

description: Now away from the Platform going off into the Phantom Forest the memories
of the train still haunt you.  You are glad to be off.
6896.name: Leading Away From The Rail Road

description: You're on Devils Road climbing a small mountain.  The trees seem to reach
for the sky even though the hill looks too steep to grow.
6710.name: Devils Road

description: Judge Dread would not like you poking around his office.  You might want
to get out of here.  A large desk with tons of papers sits in the middle of
the room.  A large sofa chair sits behind the desk.
6798.name: Judge Dread's Private Office

description: You step out of the elevator and into a large room.  You see the walls
are painted to look like the 1950's world fair.  You see a door to the south
and a large room to the east.
6857.name: {RO{7O{&J{B Zozo Headquarters{x

description: {*| {&This area was created in November/December 1997        {* |
{*| {&!This area was created by Nisstyre Bloodstoner         {* |
{*| {&This area was created for Waterdeep "City of Splendors"{* |
{*| {&This Is COPYRIGHT WATERDEEP1.0 1997-1998               {* |
You stand in front of large gates...smashed open against the wall.
People walk around inside the walls, so the city is not in any danger.
You see a large plaque on the wall.
Large iron letters over the gate read "Wel ome To  he C ty Of Z Zo"
6724.name: {r[ {MSouthern {cGate {Bof {mZ{*o{mZ{*o {CC{city {r]{x

description: A cat screams as you walk by its trash can home.  Homeless bums sit
between the trash cans asking if you could spare a couple of silver.  The
alley goes east and west.
6759.name: {g[ {*N{&ort{&h {cAlley {rRoad {g]{x

description: Welcome to "Joe's Legal and Illegal Weapons Emporium".  Here is where you
can find all kinds of weapons illegal and legal.  But in Zozo there is no
such thing as illegal.  All the walls are covered in different weapons from
swords to clubs to brass knuckles.
6762.name: Joe's Legal and Illegal Emporium

description: You are now walking through hills and trees. The road goes west to east.
6705.name: Devils Road

description: The Elevator Buttons...
| B  Lobby  2  3  4  5  6  7  8  9  10   | {G[ {gROOF {G]{x
You stand inside an elevator. A sign hangs here with the numbers of
floors. The button [ROOF] is lit up.
6898.name: Elevator at the Roof

description: Beggar's Row goes east and west.  A large doorway is to the north.  You
look up at the tower.  Lightning strikes the top of it, sending sparks
flying down.  A fire escape circles around the tower.
6728.name: {g[ {yBe{Ygg{yer's {mR{*ow {g] {rSouth {mZ{*o{mZ{*o To{mw{*er {&Sq{7ua{&re{x

description: You enter another low-class car.  Everything in here is burnt and rotting
off the walls.  Tons of ghosts wander in here searching for a soul to take
and a new life to live.
6887.name: Car 8

description: You step into the caboose of the Phantom Train.  As you step into the car
the floor below you jolts and you feel like you are moving.  You look out
the backend and see the train has departed...  But to where is it going?
6872.name: Caboose Of The Phantom Train

description: You walk into the small valley, the road goes north from here.
6722.name: Into the Valley

description: You stand at the northeast corner of Alley Road.  The alley turns here
and goes south.  The ruins of a guard tower stand here.  Most of the stones
from it lay on the ground.
6758.name: Corner of {g[ {*No{&rthea{*st {g]{B and {g[ {*N{&ort{&h {cAlley {rRoad {g]{x

description: The road here starts going down the mountain.  Below you there is a
valley.
6713.name: Starting Down The Small Mountain

description: You stand at the northwest corner of Alley Road.  Here the alley turns
and goes either south or east.  A large guard tower stands above you.
6742.name: Corner of {g[ {*No{&rthwe{*st {g]{B and {g[ {*N{&ort{&h {cAlley {rRoad {g]{x

description: {^You stand at the back wall of the club.  You see a large crowd up ahead
dancing and bashing into each other.  A band in large costumes plays a very
heavy song that almost drowns out the crowd.  You see that everyone here is
evil, high, and having the time of their life.  {x
6814.name: Inside The Club

description: You stand in a small room with very high ceiling.  You see two large
doors to the east marked Library.  The room here has paintings on it of ZoZo
back when it was new.
6807.name: Entrance To The Library

description: You stand at the southwest corner of the tower.  A shop to the south is a
condemned building.  The windows are boarded up and a sign reading
"Condemned" hangs off a nail.
6729.name: {g[ {yBe{Ygg{yer's {mR{*ow {g] {rSouthwest {mZ{*o{mZ{*o To{mw{*er {&Sq{7ua{&re{x

description: You enter a private car.  A bed, table and other things you need to live
from are here.  Funny, what do you need to live on a train full of ghosts?
An actual person is sitting in the chair, writing into a book.
6885.name: Car 7

description: Welcome to the ZoZo City Jail.  As you look around you see that this room
has not been used in a long time.  The jail cell to the east is hanging
open.  Spider webs have been made between the bars.  A desk is here with old
papers, and a lamp sits here, covered in spider webs.  Water falls in
through the window from the rain outside.
6794.name: City Jail

description: Lost in a place of grass, you wander near a large
building. Silence grows and darkness stays. No
living sounds come from the building within. A
single light shines above a sign that reads
' Doma Railways '
6867.name: Outside Alley Road

description: Inside this almost dead building, you see people, none of them speak, but
they line up collecting tickets and walking out onto the platform.
Everything has a black appearance to you.  It's almost like you are looking
at this in black-and-white.
6868.name: Doma Rail Station

description: Welcome to the News Department of Zozo.  Also here you find a desk,
with a stack of papers piling up on it.  You see the last newspaper
hanging on the wall, the date reads 1247...  The window to the south
overlooks Beggars Row, and the southern streets of Zozo.  The black
buildings and gangs move around the city.
6851.name: The News Department

description: A huge garbage pile is here.  It must be where the city puts its garbage
when they don't throw it on the streets.
6744.name: {g[ {*No{&rthwe{*st {cAlley {rRoad {g]{x

description: You stand in the southeast corner of the tower.  Some benches are here
for people to sit on.
6779.name: Southeast Corner  Of The Lobby

description: There are some more buildings here.  The large tower is straight ahead.
Beggar's Row goes to the left and right ahead circling the tower.
6727.name: {g[ {yBe{Ygg{yer's {mR{*ow {g]{x

description: Welcome To The Bar Of The Last Drink.  This bar is well kept.  Here is
where most of the travelers come to have a drink and some fun.  A large guy
stands behind the bar serving drinks.  To the north is the game room and to
the south is the lounge.
6766.name: Bar Of The Last Drink

description: You stand in a blank area of Alley Road.  You begin to wonder why the
alley is so empty here.  It's almost like something is taking all the trash
away.
6749.name: {g[ {*S{&out{&h {cAlley {rRoad {g]{x

description: You stand in the main part of the city hall.  A large round table
stands in the middle of the room.  One of the only bright light in
here hangs from the ceiling, emitting a magical glow.  On the table,
you see a large map of Zozo, the whole city, unripped, uncut.  Several
Chairs are lined up around the table...
6852.name: The Meeting Hall

description: To the west is the ZoZo tower, on which you can park your airship,
and to the north is a floating platform, on which is based the Zozo
Courier.
6700.name: The Zozo Airship Landing Area

description: To the east is a road leading towards a bay in the Dragon Sea.  To the
west is some dirty little shop.
6737.name: {g[ {yBe{Ygg{yer's {mR{*ow {g]{x

description: You have entered into the Hallway of the 8th Floor.  This floor is the
whore house (more like apartments) of ZoZo.  You hear sounds of pleasure
come from within each room.  There is a door to the north and to the south.
Back is the elevator and the pimp's office.
6821.name: In The Hallway Of The 8th Floor

description: You step onto the platform.  The train whistle blows twice calling out to
all telling it that it is departing.  The brakes release hissing with the
sound of steam, the wheels scream in agony as the train begins to move
foward.  The train departs from this stop and from this world.
6893.name: Platform

description: The Elevator Buttons...
You stand inside an elevator. A sign hangs here with the numbers of
floors. The button #10 is lit up.
6791.name: Elevator At Tenth Floor

description: {^You stand in the corner of the nightclub.  People sit in bean bags
making out and feeling each other up.  You feel the warmth of sex within
this corner.  A speaker has been mounted right above this corner and is
making very loud music.  This corner is also a very unlit corner.  {x
6813.name: In The Corner Of The Club

description: You climb on top of Car 3.  The ghosts are right behind you chanting the
sentence N O E S C A P E.  There is nowhere to run, no where to hide.  The
only way is to fly across the gap between car 3 and 5.
6878.name: On Top Of Car 3

description: Ahahahahahhaahahahahahahahahahah!  Yea, right, all you see here is
empty space, a dust bunny greets you on the ground, and a mark that a
desk once stood.
6856.name: The Law Department

description: The Elevator Buttons...
You stand inside an elevator. A sign hangs here with the numbers of
floors. The button #4 is lit up.
6785.name: Elevator At Fourth Floor

description: You stand in a large alley.  Zozo is so dirty that even a small alley is
a road here.  The road goes west and behind you are the northern gates.
6740.name: {g[ {*N{&ort{&h {cAlley {rRoad {g]{x

description: Large stone steps lead up to this Church.  The front of this church is
very tall with large stained-glass windows in it.  The walls are old and
stained from the alley bums that have done weird stuff on the walls.  You
see on the very tallest top of the church a cross the size of a person.
6836.name: Steps Of The Church

description: You stand by the church altar.  It is large and made from black stone.
Statues of great saints and a great god are carved from the walls around the
alter.  The plaster here has fallen and made weird shapes and pictures in
the walls.  The small stain glass windows allow some light to be let in.
You see a door with some stairs going up here.
6844.name: By The Church Altar

description: Welcome to Jon's Grocery Shop, the one-stop shop for all your munchies.
The walls are all shelves covered with yummie food and drinks.  You see Jon
packing groceries away.  A small child stands in one of the aisles sweeping
other people's dirt.
6768.name: Jon's Grocery Shop

description: The alley here is so shaded that you can't see a thing.
6745.name: {g[ {*So{&uthwe{*st {cAlley {rRoad {g]{x

description: You see the knight's walk up to a small cliff and a very large cave.  You
here Tim The Enchanter say " The beast that guards this has a mean strek a
mile wind."  A rabbit hops out of the cave and Tim screams "LOOK!"  .  The
knights laugh at him and Tim argues with them.  The words "It Has Teeth This
Big!!"  Come up as Tim shows them.  One of the knights says "Go Kill It" and
the knight replies "RIGHT".  He walks down to kill the puny rabbit and Tim
yells "LOOK" and the rabbit leaps from the ground and rips the knights
throat out.  The Other Knights run to do battle with the rabbit to only come
to failure.  The portal behind you opens and draws you in, but the last
thing you see is a priest bringing the Holy Hand Grenade forth the the brave
knights.
6834.name: Cave Of Caralata

description: You stand in front of the north face of the tower.  Large doors lead
south into the building and Beggar's Row goes north, east, and west.
6732.name: {g[ {yBe{Ygg{yer's {mR{*ow {g] {RNorth {mZ{*o{mZ{*o To{mw{*er {&Sq{7ua{&re{x

description: You stand in this once holy place.  The plaster that once made up the
ceilings and walls now lies on the ground.  The rows of benches still line
the aisle that still leads up to the alter.  Here and there rows of benches
have been moved to they are not perfect anymore.  The carpet on the aisle
has been pulled up to use as beds.  Some light comes in from the stained
glass windows all around you.
6838.name: Church

description: You stand on top of a small mountain.  From here you can see New Thalos,
The Dragon Sea, and even Westbridge.  The road goes north.
6711.name: On Top Of A Small Mountain

description: The blankness of the alley continues here.
6753.name: {g[ {*So{&uthea{*st {cAlley {rRoad {g]{x

description: You stand in front of two large doors.  On one door a sign reads "Court".
On the other "Room".  A door leads east out to the fire escape, but the door
is bolted shut.
6796.name: In Front Of The Court Room

description: {^{xYou{x are looking out the window of the tower.  You see the city of
ZoZo spread outwards.  You can see the Dragon Sea from this altitude.  There
is a fire escape outside here waiting for you to use it.  As you look out
the music is beginning to drown out as you stare out into the city.  {x
6818.name: In The Club By The Window

description: Welcome to the Dragon Hoard Merchants floor.  Here is where the major
merchants rule.  The Dragon Hoard merchants are a clan of merchants who
search the lands for items and sell them to investors.  There is a door to
the south and the hall goes east.
6799.name: Dragon Hoard Merchants

description: You are within the Zozo Courier Checkpoint.  To the east is a
platform on which airships may be parked, and to the south west is the
ZoZo Tower.
6721.name: The Zozo Courier Checkpoint

description: You stand in the valley.  The trees here seem to be growing fine, but
everything seems dark.  Devil's Road continues north over a hill.  To the
east, The Ancient Cliffs Of Zozo can be seen, guarding the lands from the
Sea Of Swords.  Also a road leads off in that distance, and the walls of a
fort can be seen.
6717.name: Valley

description: You stand in the southwest corner of the tower.  Some benches are here
for people to sit on.
6780.name: Southwest Corner Of The Lobby

description: Watch For Falling Objects
You walk up a steep hill. The path here turns sharply to the east, avoiding
a very steep hill. A sign is posted here.
6704.name: Up A Large Hil "Devils Road"

description: You stand inside the basement of the tower.  To the south is a large
bolted door with the words painted on it: {!  Jail{x.  The door looks like
it has not opened in years.  A door to the east is open just a little bit.
A sign on the door reads "City Morgue"
6792.name: In The Basement Of The Tower

description: You are one more car ahead from where you can board.  The only way here
is south.
6870.name: Railroad Platform

description: You stand in a large meeting hall.  A large round table sits in the
middle of the room.
6862.name: {RO{7O{&J{B Zozo Headquarters{x

description: You stand in one corner where devices big and small have been placed on
shelves to be looked over.
6860.name: {RO{7O{&J{B Zozo Headquarters{x

description: Car 2 is a lower class car.  The cushions and curtains are not as good.
Most of the curtains here have rotted totally away and the cushions are gone
off the benches.
6875.name: Car 2

description: You enter Car 3, which looks very much like Car 2. You
notice the door is blocked by a hooded figure. Ghosts appear
out of nowhere, chanting a horrid sentence.
N O  E S C A P E.
6877.name: Car 3

description: The Elevator Buttons...
You stand inside an elevator. A sign hangs here with the numbers of
floors. The button #6 is lit up.
6787.name: Elevator At Sixth Floor

description: You stand in a blank part of the alley.  Here there is nothing but the
east wall and the back of a building.
6754.name: {g[ {*So{&uthea{*st {cAlley {rRoad {g]{x

description: Trash cans line the wall here.  Wild cats and dogs look through them,
looking for a piece of meat.  Some dirty bums sit here, looking at you.
6747.name: {g[ {*So{&uthwe{*st {cAlley {rRoad {g]{x

description: The room is full of antiques.  You see old chairs and statues.  You see
the Antique Guy cleaning some furniture off ready to sell.  The whole
building is nothing but old shit which is very very boring to look at.  The
only thing that catches your eye is a glowing sword.
6769.name: Antique Guy's Antique Store

description: Danger. The Train is very dangerous, the exits behind you will dissappear and
you will be trapped with the ghosts. Only the brave enter. The whole train is
a death trap with no way out and no recalling. The only way out besides
immortal help is to kill the train and exit.
You are standing on the platform outside the station.  A large black
rotting train is parked on the rails, loading passengers and getting ready
to depart from this station, maybe even this plane.  A sign hangs here.  In
big letters it says PLEASE READ IT!
6869.name: Railroad Platform

description: You fall into a clearing in the woods.  You see the brave knights stopped
by a tall knight total dressed in black.  The tall black knight yells the
hideous and horrid word >>> NEE <<< and the brave knights cower.  Other
small black knights join in like a chorus saying >>> NEE <<<.  You overhear
the tall black knight saying 'You must find a SHRUBBERY!  ' All the brave
knights cringe.  They agree to find one.
6831.name: In A Clearing In The Woods

description: You stand in Mad Dog's Potions.  Here is where everybody in Zozo gets
their magical potions.  Mad Dog sits behind a desk.  He even looks like a
dog.  The walls are covered in shelves holding different kinds of potions.
6765.name: Mad Dog's Potions

description: You are midway down the hill.  You begin to enter the vally below.  The
clouds overhead seem dark.  You see a city with tall buildings, almost like
small towers up ahead.  It is dark and raining there.
6715.name: Midway Down

description: You stand at the southwest corner of the alley.  A guard tower is here
still standing.  It is a tall tower, probably tall enough to see the whole
city.  Alley Road turns northwards here.
6748.name: Corner of {g[ {*So{&uthwe{*st {g]{B and {g[ {*S{&out{&h {cAlley {rRoad {g]{x

description: You enter Car 1.  Rows and rows of benches for passengers line the car.
It must have been a high class passenger car.  The seat cushions are ripped
and torn.  The curtains are rotting off of their bars and the smell of mold
and rot hits your nose.
6873.name: Car 1

description: You stand at the end of the great hall looking out into the streets
below.  You see some agents who have window seats in this place.
6859.name: {RO{7O{&J{B Zozo Headquarters{x

description: You step into a large club. Music is playing all around you, people
speak from within their cave of this night club. People dance and
laugh as the band on the stage plays very heavy music. A nice
{^Icy Blue Color falls over you. You have now entered......
<-=The Reaper Nightclub=->{x
6812.name: Outside The Elevator

description: Outside Cars 1 and 2.  The only way is north into Car 2.
6874.name: Between Car 1 & 2

description: You stand at the bottom of a large hill.
6718.name: Bottom Of A Hill

description: The Reception Hall is where wedding parties and all other kinds of shit
would happen here. The hall's plaster has fallen and many many tables
lay on the ground. A once grand light fixture swang from the ceiling
now is being held up by two old wires.
6842.name: Reception Hall

description: The Elevator Buttons...
You stand inside an elevator. A sign hangs here with
the numbers of floors. The button #2 is lit up.
6783.name: Elevator At Second Floor

description: The room is filled with armor ranging from wood to chain mail.  You see
Hilt putting small rings together to make a chain mail vest.  The walls are
covered with new and used armor.  You see some bright as day, others dented
and holding some dead family's symbol.
6763.name: Hilt's Armor Shop

description: You stand inside this old empty church.  You stand where people once
gathered before a priest who went on and talked about life.  The walls here
are old and the plaster has cracked falling down.  An old table with only
three legs sits on its side.  The left over cloth from a bums bed still sits
in the corner of this room.  To The North is the Chruch itself.
6837.name: Inside The Church

description: You stand on top of a large hill.  You can see the Dragon Sea to the east
and New Thalos to the west.
6707.name: On Top Of A Hill

description: Entering the dining car, you smell food.  Strange to have food on this
train, where nothing but ghosts wander around searching for a new life.  A
table is here in the middle of the room and a ghost awaits to take your
order.
6883.name: Car 6

description: You stand at the Church of Zozo.  A sign on the corner reads "Alley
Road".  The gates are closed and a large steel chain is wrapped around both
gates with a huge iron lock holding it together.  You see steps leading up
to the church from here.
6739.name: Intersection of {yBe{Ygg{yer's {mR{*ow {B& {*N{&orth {cAlley {rRoad{x

description: You are now transferred to a cliff.  A man with a large beard stands
casting fireball spells that burst against the side of the cliffs.  You now
see the knights walking up to him.  You hear the enchanter say "My Name Is
TIM THE ENCHANTER".  They talk back and forth and then the Enchanter says,
"Follow me."
6833.name: On The Cliffside

description: On top of the church on its holy roof.  The roof has not been blessed but
it is full of holes that let the water fall into and make the church rot
even faster.  The roof makes a small noise right before a piece falls in.
6848.name: On The Roof Of The Church

description: You stand in a large lobby of the tower.  The inside looks like it once
was a great tower, but now, it looks like the rest of the city.  The only
exit out is south.
6773.name: South Entrance

description: {^BANG!  SMASH!  You get hit by people moshing.  The music here is very
loud and invites you to join in the fun.  All the nightclub members dance
here to the very fast music.  You feel your head spinning as the music takes
over your body.  You see the band up ahead.  {x
6815.name: In The Center Of The Club

description: You are now on a huge cross that is almost the size of a person.  You can
climb up and sit on it and overlook the whole city of ZoZo.  You see all
around you the city and its alley system that seems to go to nowhere.  You
see bums collecting food for themselves and other people.  You see the life
of a city...
6847.name: Cross

description: You walk for miles.  The field ends here and the snow-capped mountains
begin.  You look up at a winding path leading up and around mountains.
6703.name: Devils Road

description: You stand in the middle of the hill.  To the east is the Dragon Sea, to
the west are large snow-capped mountains.
6720.name: Middle Of A Hill

description: You once again are thrown through some kind of portal and now you stand
in the woods.  You hear three voices say "{#Halt!  Who goes there?  {x".
You see some knights ride up to a huge knight with three heads.  The knights
talk to the three-headed knight.  All of a sudden the three headed knight
heads begin to argue over something.  Without the knight noticing, the
knight runs away.  His band begins to play a nice strange tune.
6830.name: In The Forest

description: You stand in the office of the pimp.  The walls are covered with not
books, but whips and chains.  His desk stands here with a stack of gold on
it.  You see the pimp sitting behind his desk, all happy like.  You see a
whore stuffed under the desk doing something...
6825.name: Pimp Daddy G's Office

description: Bums here seem to look at you, with your armor shining in their fires.
Some even look like they might even kill you.
6751.name: {g[ {*S{&out{&h {cAlley {rRoad {g]{x

description: You stand in a large hallway on the second floor.  To the north are large
windows looking out upon the city.  To the east is a large door with a name
tag on it reading "Judge Dread".
6795.name: Hallway on the Second Floor

description: You step into an alley.  In most cities this would be the common small
dirty alley.  But in Zozo it's a street.  The alley runs between the
northern wall and the buildings southwards.
6760.name: {g[ {*N{&ort{&h {cAlley {rRoad {g]{x

description: {^YOU'RE ON STAGE.  The band looks at you saying probably 'What the
fuck?!?  '.  The stage is large and filled with lights.  The Band is getting
made.  Leave this place NOW!!!  {x
6816.name: On The Stage

description: You stand at the southeast corner of Alley road. Here the road
goes north or west. West you can see the southern gates.
6752.name: Corner of {g[ {*So{&uthea{*st {g]{B and {g[ {*S{&out{&h {cAlley {rRoad {g]{x

description: You stand on the east side of the tower.  There is a pair of large doors
here too, going into the tower.  The General Store is to the east.
6734.name: {g[ {yBe{Ygg{yer's {mR{*ow {g] {mEast {mZ{*o{mZ{*o To{mw{*er {&Sq{7ua{&re{x

description: You stand at the western face of the building.  Here there is a dirty
little shop in the building to the west.
6730.name: {g[ {yBe{Ygg{yer's {mR{*ow {g] {mWest {mZ{*o{mZ{*o To{mw{*er {&Sq{7ua{&re{x

description: You step into a car full of coal.  Tons of black coal have been loaded
into this car and awaits to be shoved into the furnace that runs this train.
You see the engine to the north.
6889.name: Coal Car

description: You stand in a very nasty bathroom.  Even though the walls are black in
here they are also stained with God Knows What.  The toilet is pink with
books to the side.  No toilet paper.
6854.name: Bathroom

description: You stand on the main street of Zozo.  The street lamps are hardly lit
and it is raining.  You look up at the tower buildings.  Up ahead is a large
tower that looks like it is almost touching the Thunder Head Clouds.  To the
east is an inn.
6725.name: {g[ {yBe{Ygg{yer's {mR{*ow {g]{x

description: You stand in the Courtroom of ZoZo.  You have the strangest feeling that
no justice ever happens here.  Benches line up straight to the judge's
bench.  Judge Dread himself is giving hell to a fragile old lady.
6797.name: Courtroom of ZoZo

description: You are between Cars 5 and 6.  The only exit is north.
6882.name: Between Cars 5 & 6

description: WOW!!!  Look at all the druggies in this corner.  Filled with people
smoking a bong and doing the crack pipe.  You see some people with a belt
around their arm and a needle in their hand.  This looks like fun to be part
of the band.  The band's cases are spread across here with these druggies
sitting on them, getting wAsTeD!!!
6817.name: In The Northeast Corner

description: You walk on a road going through a field.  The main road behind
disappears.  To the east you can see the Dragon Sea.  A sign posted here
reads "Devils Road".
6702.name: Road Named "Devils Road"

description: You stand next to the gates of Zozo.  There are really no bums here,
because there are some guards at the gates.
6761.name: {g[ {*S{&out{&h {cAlley {rRoad {g]{x

description: You are walking down the east side of Alley Road.  There is really
nothing to be seen here.
6757.name: Intersection of {*No{&rthea{*st {B& {*So{&uthea{*st {cAlley {rRoad{x

description: The northeast corner of Beggar's Row.  There are buildings to t he east
and north.  Beggar's Row goes south and west.
6733.name: {g[ {yBe{Ygg{yer's {mR{*ow {g] {RNortheast {mZ{*o{mZ{*o To{mw{*er {&Sq{7ua{&re{x

description: You are on a huge platform floating over the city of Zozo.
Cross-winds buffet you and the ships docked on the platform.  In the
center of the platform are a number of small buildings, and a larger
one with the words, "{DZozo Courier{x" painted on it.
6772.name: Zozo Courier Parking

description: The road here curves to the west.  Some of the trees here seem to have
been broken off.
6708.name: Devils Road

description: You stand in Zed's Office.
6864.name: Zed's Office

description: You stand in the Whore's Room.  A whore is laying on the bed, her clothes
lay on the ground.  A dirty adventurer kneels on top of her, making sweet
sweet love.  She moans out with every...  Oops, this is getting too dirty...
6826.name: Whore's Room

description: You stand where the chorus once sung.  An old pipe organ still sits here
and looks like it could almost be played once again.  Bleachers to hold the
holy souls stands here broken from the rain that has fallen in through the
room.  You see a very large stain glass window looking out at the buildings
that surround the church and alley system.
6845.name: Chorus

description: You stand in a large room.  Large steel cabinets with large doors on them
are here.  A large table with tools on it is here.  A bucket on the floor is
filled with blood.  Bloody tools lay on a table.
6793.name: ZoZo City Morgue

description: You stand east of the gates.  No bums are around because of the guards at
the gate.
6750.name: {g[ {*S{&out{&h {cAlley {rRoad {g]{x

description: You stand in a grubby inn, but the best inn in Zozo.  The room is dimly
lit and a dirty innkeeper stands behing a desk, enclosed in glass.  A
firepit is here in the middle of the inn.
6767.name: Zozo Inn

description: You stand in a large room.  The walls are covered with bookshelves and
books.  You read some of the titles like "Your Inner Demon" and "How To Cook
You Grandmother".  A large desk sits here with a large chair.  And in the
chair is a very large mayor.
6806.name: Mayor's Office

description: You go down a steep part in the road.  The ground here is so steep that
even trees can't grow here.
6714.name: Going Down Devil's Road

description: You stand inside the Zozo Courier offices.  A counter lines the
southern wall, and upon said counter are stacked a large number of
boxes, all apparently awating embarkation.
6839.name: The Zozo Courier

description: You walk down the dirt ridden streets of Zozo.  You shudder at the crime
going on around.  There are buildings to the left and right.  Beggar's Row
goes north.
6726.name: {g[ {yBe{Ygg{yer's {mR{*ow {g]{x

description: You stand in a large library.  The bookshelves here go straight to the
ceiling.  People are actually walking around here looking at books.
6808.name: Library Of Zozo

description: Heading north on Beggar's Row.  Some dirty shops are to each side.  The
rain keeps falling.
6736.name: {g[ {yBe{Ygg{yer's {mR{*ow {g]{x

description: Alley Road goes north and south here.  Bums sit all around you.  A pair
of bums stand around a barrel that has burning trash in it.
6756.name: {g[ {*So{&uthea{*st {cAlley {rRoad {g]{x

description: The glowing fire lights of ZoZo dim out.  You are in the middle of a
grassland.  Total darkness is your friend.  The only directions here are
west and east.
6866.name: Outside Alley Road

description: In Car 5 it looks like the other high-class cars.  Ghosts wander around
in here searching for a soul to steal.  The only way out here is to wrestle
the key away from the ghost.
6881.name: Car 5

description: You stand in the Whore's Room.  A whore is laying on the bed, her clothes
lay on the ground.  A dirty adventurer kneels on top of her, making sweet
sweet love.  She moans out with every...  Oops, this is getting too dirty...
6823.name: Whore's Room

description: The Elevator Buttons...
You stand inside an elevator. A sign hangs here with the numbers of
floors. The button #5 is lit up.
6786.name: Elevator At Fifth Floor

description: Alley road goes west and east here.  Some garbage cans lay here on their
side with dogs picking through them.
6741.name: {g[ {*N{&ort{&h {cAlley {rRoad {g]{x

description: You stand in the lounge area.  A large couch stands here, facing to
the east out the window, overlooking the east side of Zozo and the Sea
Of Swords.  A large coffee table sits infront of the couch, a
cigarette ashtray lies on top, and some magizines lay next to it.
6855.name: The Lounge

description: Opening a small trap door in the ceiling you get onto the steeple of the
church.  You can go up and climb its steep roof to the huge cross that
overlooks the whole city.  You can also reach the more flat room to the
north to stand on.
6846.name: Steeple

description: You stand in the hallway on the third floor.  Large doors lay to the
south and a small door marked "Fire Exit" lays to the north.
6803.name: Hallway On The Third Floor

description: Welcome to the mayor's office.  A secretary sits here, working on her
nails.  She totally ignores you.  A pair of large doors lay to the south
marked "Mayor".
6805.name: Mayor's Office

description: You stand in a large library.  The bookshelves here go straight to the
ceiling.  People are actually walking around here looking at books.
6811.name: Library Of Zozo

description: You stand in a dimly lit hallway.  You see the hall go eastwards across
the tower.  Doors on either side of the hall line straight down to the end
of the tower.  Muffled human sounds come from within.  You see a door to the
south that reads 'Pimp Office'.
6820.name: Hallway Outside The Elevator

description: The echo of once people's voices hit the walls and into your ears.  This
room once housed many meetings and bingo sessions that were held in this
church.  Old tables line the floor and walls either standing or crushed.
The windows in this room seem to show that people have been in here throwing
stones through them.
6840.name: Chruch Meeting Hall

description: You stand in the Dragon Hoard Meeting Room.  Here is where all the head
members come and sit at a large table.  A large chair sits at the far end
here.  There are many chairs, four on each side.  You see one side say West
and the other side say East.
6802.name: Dragon Hoard Meeting Room

description: {*|  {&Now Entering   {*|
{*|  {&The City Of    {*|
You are almost to the dark city ahead.  A sign has been posted here, and
it protrudes crookedly from the ground.
6723.name: Devils Road

description: This room is empty.
6861.name: {RO{7O{&J{B Zozo Headquarters{x

description: You stand in a large rooms where agents are working.  You also see to one
side creatures being interviewed by other agents.
6858.name: {RO{7O{&J{B Zozo Headquarters{x

description: You are thrown into the town square.  You look back at the field but...
IT'S NOT THERE.  You stand in a large town square.  A crowd of local farmers
drags a woman with a cucumber on her nose up to a noble knight standing on a
platform.  You hear the shouts of the crowd say "SHE'S A WITCH!  A WITCH!"
You see the knights from the field ride up and talk to the noble knight.
They put the women on a scale with a chicken on the other side.  When she
goes down and the chicken goes up everyone cheers and she is dragged off.
You then see the noble knight and the other knights ride off south.
6829.name: In The Town Square

description: You are between the Coal Car and the Locomotive.  The only exit is north.
6890.name: Between Coal Car and Locomotive

description: This area of the Alley seems to be burned from the building next door.
The ground seems to be burnt and a horrible smell is here.
6746.name: {g[ {*So{&uthwe{*st {cAlley {rRoad {g]{x

description: The Elevator Buttons...
You stand inside an elevator. A sign hangs here with the numbers of
floors. The button #7 is lit up.
6788.name: Elevator At Seventh Floor

description: You stand in a large library.  The bookshelves here go straight to the
ceiling.  People are actually walking around here looking at books.
6810.name: Library Of Zozo

description: The Elevator Buttons...
You stand inside an elevator. A sign hangs here with the numbers of
floors. The button #8 is lit up.
6789.name: Elevator At Eighth Floor

description: The Elevator Buttons...
You stand inside an elevator. A sign hangs here with
the numbers of floors. The button Lobby is lit up.
6776.name: Elevator At Lobby

description: You stand in what looks like a small kitchen area.  A coffee maker
stands on the marble countertops to the north, and some cabinets hang
above it.  A large iron fridge stands to the east of the counter, and
a stove to the west.  A kitchen table stands in this small area, a
candle sits on it, burning.  Another ashtray and some magizines lies
on the table here too.  A door to the east reads "Bathroom".
6853.name: The Eating Area

description: You are between Cars 6 and 7. The only exit is north.
6884.name: Between Car 6 & 7

description: You are walking down the streets of Zozo.  The rain is still coming down
just as hard as when you came in.  North of you are the northern gates to
the city.  And from what you can see there is a small alley going in both
directions from the gate.
6738.name: {g[ {yBe{Ygg{yer's {mR{*ow {g]{x

description: Here you stand at a back of a mess hall.  Trash cans are being raided by
bums looking for some food to fill their empty stomachs.
6755.name: {g[ {*So{&uthea{*st {cAlley {rRoad {g]{x

description: You stand in a large game room.  A dart board hangs on the northern wall.
A large pool table sits in the middle of the room.  Some other games sit
around the pool table.  A large chalkboard hangs on the wall for people to
keep score.
6800.name: Game Room

description: The northwest corner of Beggar's Row.  A ladder is here coming off the
fire escape of the building.  There are some shops here to the north and
west.
6731.name: {g[ {yBe{Ygg{yer's {mR{*ow {g] {RNorthwest {mZ{*o{mZ{*o To{mw{*er {&Sq{7ua{&re{x

description: You are between Cars 2 & 3. The only way is north.
6876.name: Between Car 2 & 3

description: You stand at the south end of the platform.  The only way around is north.
6895.name: Platform

description: You land on top of Car 5.  The ghosts behind you cannot follow.  They are
still chanting the words N O E S C A P E.  The only way is down.
6880.name: On Top Of Car 5

description: You enter the valley floor.  The road here goes north towards a large
city with tall buildings.
6716.name: Valley Floor

description: The Elevator Buttons...
You stand inside an elevator. A sign hangs here with the numbers of
floors. The button #3 is lit up.
6784.name: Elevator At Third Floor

description: This is a small store room where stuff was kept to be safe.  There is
nothing more except it looks like every other room, paint peeling, plaster
falling down.
6841.name: Store Room

description: You stand on top of a small hill.  You can see the city from here.  The
path goes north.
6719.name: On Top Of The Hill

description: You stand in a room.
6863.name: {RO{7O{&J{B Zozo Headquarters{x

description: You step into the Locomotive. It seems to shake from
your presence, shaking in anger. A pain strikes your
head like a blow from a war axe. A deep loud voice echos
in your head:
" HOW DARE YOU BOARD THIS TRAIN, WITH YOUR LIVING SOUL. "
" NOW YOU MUST FACE ME TO LEAVE THIS PLACE OF DEATH.    "
The Phantom Train awaits your attack.
6891.name: On The Locomotive

description: You stand at the north end of the platform.  The only way around is south.
6894.name: Platform

description: You stand in the Whore's Room.  A whore is laying on the bed, her
clothes lay on the ground.  A dirty adventurer kneels on top of her, making
sweet sweet love.  She moans out with every...  Oops, this is getting too
dirty...
6827.name: Whore's Room

description: You stand in a large library.  The bookshelves here go straight to the
ceiling.  People are actually walking around here looking at books.
6809.name: Library Of Zozo

description: You are between Cars 8 and the coal car.  The only exit is north.
6888.name: Between Car 8 and the Coal Car

description: Dead Man's Curse, Watch You Step, Its A Long Ways Down.
Devil's Road turns sharply to the east here.  A sign is posted next to a
cliff.
6712.name: Bend In The Road

description: You are floating between the two cars.  You wonder where Car 4 is.  The
only way is north onto Car 5.
6879.name: Jumping Across Between Cars 3 & 5

description: You continue down Devil's Road. The path turns upwards to pass a large hill.
6706.name: Devil's Road

description: You are on a road leading northwards away from New Thalos towards the
snow-capped mountains.
6701.name: Turn Off OF The Main Road

description: The Elevator Buttons...
You stand inside an elevator. A sign hangs here with the numbers
of floors. The button B is lit up.
6782.name: Basement

description: You stand in the Northeast corner of the tower.  Some benches are here
for people to sit on.
6777.name: Northeast Corner Of The Lobby

description: You stand in a large lobby of the tower.  The inside looks like it once
was a great tower, but now, it looks like the rest of the city.  The only
exit out is west.
6781.name: West Entrance

description: You stand on the corner of Beggar's Row.  The road goes north.  There is
a building to the east here.  The building east looks blackened with fire.
A potion shop is to the south.
6735.name: {g[ {yBe{Ygg{yer's {mR{*ow {g] {rSoutheast {mZ{*o{mZ{*o To{mw{*er {&Sq{7ua{&re{x

description: Devil's Road goes up over a hill here.  The winds to the north begin to
blow, a cold icy chill comes over you.
6709.name: Devils Road

description: You stand in the middle of the lobby.  From here there are doors leading
out in all directions.  To the northwest there is a crude elevator.
6774.name: Middle Of The Lobby

description: You stand in a large room.  Here there are many desks with lamps on them
and papers.  This room is where all the orders for Dragon Hoard come in.  A
huge printing press lays in the west corner with paper stacked in it.
6804.name: Dragon Hoard Offices

description: Welcome to the Lounge, a great place to rest.  The room seems to hum with
some sort of healing power.  The chairs and couches seem to hum the same
way.  A female stands singing by some guys playing music in the corner.  The
lights are turned down really low and a weird light show comes from the
glowing ball in the middle of the room.
6801.name: Lounge

description: A nice plate glass window looks out over the buildings across the street.
You see the shops below on Beggar's Row.  Doors are to the north and south
with nice sounds coming from within....  Human sounds....  People having
pleasure.  The hallway goes back to the west.
6822.name: End Of The Hallway

description: You are now standing at the Bridge Of Death.  The brave knights are here
and a really old dirty looking man stands here.  A knight goes up to the man
and the old man asks three questions.  The knight gets them right and walks
across the bridge.  A second knight comes up to the old man and he is asked
three questions.  The knight makes a mistake and is cast into the fiery
canyon below the bridge.  The third knight comes up at the old man a passes
the three questions.  The last knight comes up to the old man and is asked
the three questions.  He passes.  Now it's your turn.  Do you wish to cross
the Bridge Of Doom.
6835.name: Bridge Of Death

description: You stand in the old kitchen. Food was made here to serve the bingo hall
and the reception hall. Food for the poor and the priests where also
made here. The sounds of water boiling and meat being chopped up can be
heard almost in an freaky past sound.
6843.name: Kitchen

description: What a place.  This is Sydney's Magic shop and Gift cards.  All the walls
are covered with wands and staffs and gift cards?!?!?  Makes you wonder in
this kind of town why someone would sell cards.
6764.name: Sydney's Magic Shop and Gift Cards

6700.room_name: An invisable specter floats above all here.
6700.name: An invisable specter~

description: It's a dirty, filthy dog that is looking for food.  KICK IT!
6701.room_name: A filthy dog slinks around in the shadows, looking for food.
6701.name: A filthy dog~

description: You see a pussy hissing at you. MEOW!
6702.room_name: An alley cat hisses at your presence and your light.
6702.name: an alley cat~

6703.d_flags: D Screams 'You could have just spared some change... Jesus Christ!!'~
description:
You see a filthy dirty bum here asking you for some spare change.
He is dressed like a bum and smells like a bum.
6703.room_name: A bum is here begging you for some spare change.
6703.name: The Bum~

6704.d_flags: D Screams 'HAIL ZOZO, I may have died but i say FUCK YOU!'~
description:
They are one of the famous citizens of Zozo.  They think they
are high and mighty, living in this grand city.  Damn, this city is
more like a paradise for white trash and scum.  Just splatter their 
brains all over the street, please.
6704.room_name: A citizen of Zozo walks around here and snickers at your presence.
6704.name: A Citizen of Zozo~

6705.d_flags: D Screams 'I fought to the end and now I may rest in hell!'~
description: He is here to protect and serve all evil!
6705.room_name: A guard of the Royal ZoZo police walks around here.
6705.name: a guard of ZoZo~

6706.d_flags: D Screams 'I fought to the end to save me beer, well maybe there is beer heaven!'~
description: The Guard DID protect evil, now he's just protecting his beer.
6706.room_name: A drunk ZoZo guard stumbles around here.
6706.name: a drunk ZoZo guard~

6708.d_flags: D Screams 'But I had a tea party with the Queen, well bloody damn!!'~
description:
They are just like every other citizen but they have a few more gold
pieces in their pouch.  They think they are higher than anyone else on the
planet.
6708.room_name: A higher-class citizen walks around here like a snob.
6708.name: a higher-class citizen~

6709.d_flags: D Screams 'MY TAX MONEY, ALL MY GLORIOUS TAX MONEY GONE, ALL GONE!!!'~
description:
He's fat, rich and looks like scum.  He is the mayor of ZoZo and he likes
to collect taxes.  He makes you think of that 4000-pound woman you saw in
the National Enquirer.
6709.room_name: You see the Mayor of ZoZo walking around here.
6709.name: Mayor Samton of ZoZo~

6710.d_flags: D Screams 'At least I got my money!!'~
description:
He gets the mayor all his money.  But he doubles the tax so he gets money
from it.  He looks rich like the mayor and snobby like the high class
citizens, SIC HIM, KILL HIM!!
6710.room_name: The Tax Collector of Zozo is walking around getting his share of taxes.
6710.name: the tax collector~

6711.d_flags: D Screams 'I TOLD YOU ALL TO SHUT THE FUCK UP GOD DAMN IT!'~
description: You've always hated them, now you can KILL THEM. KILL HER!!!
6711.room_name: The Librarian stands here shushing everyone to be {#quiet{x.
6711.name: the Librarian~

6712.d_flags: D Screams 'I NEVER FINISHED WAR AND PEACE YOU FRIGGIN' CAVE MAN!'~
description:
It's one of those people that LIKE coming to the library.  They always
did well in school and think you're some dumb cave man.  Why don't you bash
their head in?
6712.room_name: A Book Reader is here reading a very very large book.
6712.name: a Book Reader~

6713.d_flags: D Screams 'I HAVE DIED FOR MY CLAN THE DRAGON HOARD!!'~
description:
They work for 'The Fox' getting his info on ancient objects that his
people are finding all around the lands.
6713.room_name: A Dragon Hoard office worker stands here getting some info from merchants.
6713.name: a Dragon Hoard office worker~

6714.d_flags: D Screams 'I HAVE DIED FOR MY CLAN THE DRAGON HOARD!!'~
description:
They just came back from a far off land to get an ancient object for 'The
Fox'.
6714.room_name: A merchant of the Dragon Hoard stands here, back from an adventure.
6714.name: a merchant of the Dragon Hoard~

6715.d_flags: D Screams 'YOU'RE GOING TO THE CHAIR, YOU BASTARD!!'~
description:
He is big, wears a black judge's robe with big white letters that say
"THE JUDGE".  He is the law, so why don't you show him some?
6715.room_name: "THE JUDGE" stands here about to send someone to the electric chair.
6715.name: THE JUDGE~

6716.d_flags: D Screams 'GOD DAMN IT I WANTED TO SEND THAT GUY TO THE CHAIR!!'~
description: They are a jury member.  Kill them!
6716.room_name: A jury member sits here, listening to the lawyer.
6716.name: a jury member~

6717.d_flags: D Screams 'BUT I LIKE TO PLAY WITH THE DEAD!'~
description:
He is a sick little puppy.  He likes to dress up the dead and make
puppets out of them.  Maybe you should help him.  I think his skull is very
fragile.
6717.room_name: The morgue person stands here, looking at the dead.
6717.name: the morgue person~

description:
Marshals where suppose to protect the good and innocent. But since
this whole city is crooked he protects the evil and guilty.
6718.room_name: The Marshal of ZoZo stands here, protecting the evil people.
6718.name: the Marshal of ZoZo~

6719.d_flags: D Screams 'AH! THANK YOU!! DEATH IS FREEDOM!!!!'~
description:
He was locked up for helping an old lady cross the street.  It went fine
until the marshal ran over the lady with his steed.
6719.room_name: A prisoner stands here, asking to be released from this cell.
6719.name: a prisoner~

6720.d_flags: D Screams 'We're here To protect and to serve!'~
description:
